From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 
From: R
Date: Sun, 25 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Force glFinish() after frame to flush XFB blit for libretro
 frontends

Dolphin's OGL backend renders into its own internal EFB FBO and blits
the final XFB image to the system framebuffer (provided by the libretro
frontend via get_current_framebuffer). However, the GL commands for
this blit may still be in the GPU pipeline when retro_run() returns.

Libretro frontends that do CPU-side readback (glReadPixels) of the
system framebuffer see black or partial frames because the blit hasn't
completed yet. Adding glFinish() after the GPU loop ensures all GL
commands — including the XFB present blit — have completed before
retro_run() returns, so the frontend reads the correct frame.

This only fires on the OGL backend path where SetSystemFrameBuffer
was already called.

diff --git a/Source/Core/DolphinLibretro/Main.cpp b/Source/Core/DolphinLibretro/Main.cpp
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/Source/Core/DolphinLibretro/Main.cpp
+++ b/Source/Core/DolphinLibretro/Main.cpp
@@ -1,5 +1,6 @@
 #include <cstdint>
 #include <libretro.h>
+#include <GL/gl.h>
 #include <string>
 #include <thread>
 #include <fstream>
@@ -350,6 +351,14 @@ void retro_run(void)
     system.GetCPU().RunSingleFrame();
   }
 
+  // Flush all pending GL commands so the XFB present blit to the
+  // system framebuffer is complete before retro_run() returns.
+  // Without this, frontends doing glReadPixels on the system FBO
+  // see black/partial frames due to in-flight GPU commands.
+  if (g_gfx && Config::Get(Config::MAIN_GFX_BACKEND) == "OGL")
+  {
+    glFinish();
+  }
 
   RETRO_PERFORMANCE_STOP(dolphin_main_func);